tr.td: The patient shows significant hyperglycemia and elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, possibly chronic kidney disease. There is also mild hyperchloremia and low total COâ, suggesting a tendency toward metabolic acidosis. Liver function, electrolytes, and lipid profile are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal status and glycemic control.
